Pauli Murray

The Rev. Dr. Pauli Murray was a trailblazing activist, legal scholar, and Episcopal priest (to name just a few). Pauli was born in Baltimore, but was raised in Durham - eventually graduating from Hillside High School in 1926. A fierce advocate for social justice, Pauli co-founded the National Organization for Women (NOW) and played a significant role in shaping landmark legal decisions, including Brown v. Board of Education. Pauli‚Äôs work continues to influence the intersection of civil rights and gender equality.

caption:
No lunch plans?? Stop by TODAY! 

ReCity is hosting [re]DINE a "pay-what-you-can" pop-up cafe supporting local farmers and chefs and providing fresh, hot, delicious meals for everyone in a "buy-one / give-one" style, while also eliminating waste. Minimum cost is $6, but feel free to pay $12 or $25 or whatever you want. 

For every meal we sell we will provide the same hot, delicious meal to one of our local neighbors who can't afford it. You're gonna eat lunch Friday somewhere (and probably spend a lot more than $6) why not Eat Good with us and Do Good at the same time. 

Please stop by between 11-2 TODAY and support Skip Gibbs with OAM/Brightwood Agriculture Group + ReCity Collaborative - 112 Broadway St, Durham.
